                            <comment id="12880969" author="emerson" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2010 01:20:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Bleh. Sorry. I&apos;m getting myself confused. In AbstractSimilarity, userSimilarity &lt;b&gt;always&lt;/b&gt; centers the data, whereas itemSimilarity is conditional. The problem, then, is with userSimilarity.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12881095" author="srowen" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2010 07:31:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds good, I think it&apos;s largely because un-centering is the exception and isn&apos;t used for user-user similarity as it happens, yet. Easy enough to change this however.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
